@node Thanks "Thanks to Arthur Pijpers"

  @{b}@{u}Thanks@{uu}@{ub}

      There exists another REKO cardset written by Arthur Pijpers. I wasn't
  happy with its performance and therefore written my own. Soon after my
  DataType was released, I got E-Mail from Arthur Pijpers with a suggestion
  to join our efforts and create a 'perfect' REKO DataType. Unfortunately,
  due to some problems on my side (like losing all mail folders) the
  cooperation never really started (though I got source for Arthur's
  DataType). And it is doubtfull that it will be possible, since my E-Mail
  is half-operational (I can receive, but not send letters). Therefore I
  decided to continue improving my source and release a new version of
  @{b}MREKO@{ub}. But feel I owe this few words to Arthur, whom you can contact at
  this E-Mail address:
    @{i}arthurp@grafix.xs4all.nl@{ui}.
  You can also get the other REKO DataType:
    @{i}Aminet://util/dtype/REKOdt392.lha@{ui}.
      
@endnode

@node Introduction "Introduction to MREKO"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

      @{b}MREKO@{ub} is a @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes} subclass for loading and displaying @{"Klondike AGA" link Klondike}
  cardsets. Once installed it will let all @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes} aware programs to
  recognize and load @{"Klondike AGA" link Klondike} cardsets.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements for MREKO"

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

      @{b}MREKO@{ub} requires AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher (@{i}datatypes.library @{ui}V39+). AGA
  chipset is recomended, since most of @{"Klondike AGA" link Klondike} cardsets use HAM(8)
  mode. Without AGA chipset those cardsets will be very distorted.
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation of MREKO"

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

      Use supplied @{i}Installer @{ui}script to copy necessary files.  If you
  go for "Manually Selectable" installation you will need to activate class
  by double-clicking on @{i}DEVS:DataTypes/REKO Cardset @{ui}icon or using
  @{i}AddDataTypes @{b}REFRESH @{ub}@{ui}from Shell.
@endnode

@node Notes "MREKO Notes"

  @{b}@{u}Notes@{uu}@{ub}

      Since version 1.2 it is possible to display both HAM(8) and color
  cardsets.
      Users without AGA chipsets will not see HAM8 cardsets.
      The DataType can deal with cardsets containing any number of cards,
  with any number of colors, and of any size.
      There are many Enforcer hits when HAM(8) cardsets are used as a
  Workbench pattern. It seems that @{i}IPrefs @{ui} doesn't support HAM(8) patterns...
@endnode

@node History "MREKO History"

  @{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

      @{b}Version 1.0 (11.4.95)@{ub} - initial release.

      @{b}Version 1.1 (22.4.95)@{ub} - limited release

    Improvements:
    · Changed layout of this document.

    Bug fixes:
    · @{b}MREKO@{ub} could not be used with @{i}IPrefs@{ui}.

      @{b}Version 1.2 (9.2.97)@{ub} - second release

    Improvements:
    · Better cards layout;
    · Shorter code.

    Bug fixes:
    · Non-HAM(8) cardsets are properly recognized and handled;
    · No more enforcer hits on non-AGA machines when loading HAM8 cardsets.
@endnode

